RWAA Org Chart — Workflow Guide
=================================
 
 
FILE DESCRIPTIONS
-----------------
 
RAW DATA (Excel — versioned by date)
  20260407_rwaa_sa_expert_cleaned.xlsx
      Self-reported expertise scores for each team member (1/2/3) across databases and tools.
      The date prefix (YYYYMMDD) is the version. When you update this file, rename it with
      today's date so previous versions are preserved (e.g. 20260501_rwaa_sa_expert_cleaned.xlsx).
 
  20260407_rwaa_sa_roles_cleaned.xlsx
      Org structure data — one row per person per assignment, containing TA, functional group,
      employment type, and role (head/lead/member). Same date-prefix versioning applies.
 
 
R SCRIPTS (run in order)
  script_expertise_excel_to_rds.R
      Reads the expertise Excel file, cleans and standardises column names, filters out
      incomplete rows, and saves the result as dat_rwaa_sa_expert_all.rds.
 
  script_roles_excel_to_rds.R
      Reads the roles Excel file, cleans column names, and saves the result as
      dat_rwaa_sa_roles.rds.
 
  script_join_expertise_and_roles.R
      Joins the expertise and roles RDS files on name, and saves the combined dataset as
      dat_rwaa_sa_team.rds. Also produces diagnostic outputs:
        - dat_rwaa_sa_expert_completed.rds  — people with complete expertise scores
        - dat_rwaa_sa_expert_missing.rds    — people missing scores (not yet submitted)
        - dat_rwaa_sa_expert_other.rds      — records that did not match between files
 
 
PYTHON SCRIPT
  build_org_chart.py
      Reads dat_rwaa_sa_team.rds (via CSV export) and generates rwaa-org-chart.html.
      Run this after the R scripts have completed.
 
 
OUTPUT
  dat_rwaa_sa_team.rds      — Final joined dataset used to build the org chart
  rwaa-org-chart.html       — The interactive org chart, ready to embed in Quarto
 
 
STEP-BY-STEP WORKFLOW
----------------------
 
Step 1 — Update your Excel files
  Edit the appropriate versioned Excel files. If making significant changes, rename the
  file with today's date before editing to preserve the previous version.
 
Step 2 — Run the R scripts in order in RStudio
  1. script_expertise_excel_to_rds.R
  2. script_roles_excel_to_rds.R
  3. script_join_expertise_and_roles.R
 
  Check dat_rwaa_sa_expert_missing.rds after Step 3 to see who has not yet submitted scores.
 
Step 3 — Generate the org chart
  Either run build_org_chart.py directly, or add this line to the bottom of
  script_join_expertise_and_roles.R to run the full pipeline in one shot:
 
      system("python3 build_org_chart.py")
 
Step 4 — Embed in Quarto
  Copy the code from the HTML file into the html chunk. Do not point to the file. If the html is directly in quarto, it will fill the page as required. If quarto merely point to an html file in the files, it will restrict the size of the html element and require and scroll bar.
 
SCORE REFERENCE
---------------
1 = Little to no experience  (no badge shown)
2 = User                     (blue badge)
3 = Professional             (purple badge)
 
 
EMPLOYMENT CODES
----------------
ft = Full-Time
pt = Part-Time
ct = Contractor
 
 
ROLE CODES
----------
head   = Group head (centered, bold, above first divider)
lead   = Lead (bold, second partition)
member = Member (plain text, third partition)